NEWTON
Now Flamsteed, suppose I do know who made the book. It contains work you have been paid to do on behalf of the crown, does it not?

FLAMSTEED
Yes. However, it appears to contain only the parts which support your theory of gravitation. Some numbers have also apparently been smoothed.

NEWTON
Not all your observations appeared to make sense.

FLAMSTEED
Yes, I see here Dr Haley called them defective and attributed it to me having bad eyesight. 

NEWTON
Dr Haley should be left out of this. Are you still bitter we forgot to credit your for that comet? That was 30 years ago.

FLAMSTEED
You still have made no effort to correct that mistake. You claimed I was wrong, then you claimed my idea as your own. And you still do, to this day. My vision may not be what it used to but yours doesn't ever extend beyond your nose.

NEWTON
Mr Flamsteed, these observations are important and they ought be circulated among those who would like to use them.

FLAMSTEED
Then why have you been so selective with it? You care not for the position of the stars but only for the lunar observation to use in the next edition of your book. 

NEWTON
As with everything there are the builders and the designers. You are a bricklayer who believes himself to be an architect.

FLAMSTEED
And you are but a man who believes himself to be a God.

NEWTON
After a point, every additional observation becomes less and less useful. You, along with Robert Hooke and that irascible pensioner Stephen Gray are merely surveyors doing repetitive remedial tasks that any child could do. 

FLAMSTEED
Those honorable men dedicated decades to science to provide the tools of discovery for everyone. You have sought to tarnish their reputations because you fear a discovery by someone other than yourself might dim your flame. 
(pause)
That must be why you have omitted the majority of my work.
(pause)
How many of these books did you make?

NEWTON
Only 400.

FLAMSTEED
400?! With this you have poisoned the well of observation from which every scientist must drink. The only thing worse than no knowledge is incorrect knowledge. And with *my name* on it!

NEWTON
Relax Mr Flamsteed, The deed is done.

FLAMSTEED
I will retrieve every copy and burn them. Then only after the complete catalog is verified, will it be published and without the liberties of Dr Haley.

NEWTON
You're 66 years old, you're 35 years into this! You will likely not live to see that through. The current state is good enough.

SOMERSET
